                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13429627" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 7 Aug 2012 00:49:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was actually a fairly bad bug as brought up on the user list a week or two back - the std zk client does not deal with connection loss well, but worse, once it&apos;s had a connection expiration, you have to make a new client - you cannot use the old one. So if the distrib queue zk client ever gets expired, it will continually hit expiration exceptions as you try to use it again - so no nodes can publish states (other issues too, but thats a big one). This can put in in an infinite recovery loop.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13429644" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 7 Aug 2012 01:20:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;reopened to change from improvement to bug&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
